el to Pick\\\",\\\"metaDescription\\\":\\\"Wondering what OpenClaw is and how to use it? This beginner-friendly OpenClaw guide covers setup, model selection, device requirements, and real-world use cases to help you get started fast.\\\",\\\"keywords\\\":\\\"openclaw, what is openclaw, how to use openclaw, openclaw guide\\\"}\",\"createTime\":\"2026-03-10 14:12:50\",\"editTime\":\"2026-03-10 14:14:52\",\"status\":1,\"language\":\"en\",\"appId\":\"gptproto.com\",\"uuidCode\":\"858e3f12512c4b349f683f4b6964f61c\",\"author\":{\"id\":4,\"name\":\"Tiffany Layne\",\"avatar\":\"https://heyoo.oss-ap-southeast-1.aliyuncs.com/2025/09/23/53a0ab25c3c743f382d6435763ec236d.png\",\"profile\":\"Tiffany Layne (Pseudonym Tiffany) studied Information Systems at Ludwig Maximilian University of Munich and earned an M.A. in Digital Marketing. Since 2013, she has been working as an editor, translator, and marketing strategist for software and AI platforms. She writes high-quality guides and insights on API-based services, AI model usage, system stability, and digital business applications, providing readers with both technical know-how and practical perspectives in the AI industry.\"},\"introduction\":\"\u003ch2\u003eTL;DR:\u003c/h2\u003e\\n\u003cp\u003eKnown as the \\\"little lobster,\\\" OpenClaw is an open-source AI agent that runs on your computer \u0026mdash; even a decade-old one \u0026mdash; and connects to any AI model via API to handle files, send emails, browse the web, and automate tasks through a simple chat app like QQ or Feishu.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"type\":\"blog\"},{\"id\":3087,\"authorId\":1,\"authorName\":\"Tiffany Layne\",\"image\":null,\"authorAvatar\":null,\"simplifiedName\":\"GPT-5.4 Is Here: Everything You Need to Know\",\"traditionalName\":\"GPT-5.4 Is Here: Everything You Need to Know\",\"englishName\":\"GPT-5.4 Is Here: Everything You Need to Know\",\"name\":\"GPT-5.4 Is Here: Everything You Need to Know\",\"shortSimplifiedContent\":\"\",\"shortTraditionalContent\":\"\",\"shortEnglishContent\":\"\",\"shortContent\":\"\",\"contentType\":\"html\",\"releaseTime\":\"2026-03-09 18:16:42\",\"readCount\":1,\"likeCount\":1,\"commentCount\":1,\"categoryID\":199,\"categoryName\":\"gptproto.com\",\"logo\":\"https://oss.gptproto.com/gptproto/ai-draw/java/test//2026/03/09/bddc72d8e1b4476a92be11a8c386923e.png\",\"metaTitle\":null,\"metaDescription\":null,\"url\":null,\"categoryVos\":null,\"tagVos\":null,\"categoryUuid\":\"gptproto.com\",\"uuid\":\"gpt-5-4-complete-guide\",\"seo\":\"{\\\"metaTitle\\\":\\\"GPT-5.4: Everything You Need to Know About OpenAI's Most Powerful Model\\\",\\\"metaDescription\\\":\\\"GPT-5.4 is OpenAI's latest AI model, combining advanced reasoning, coding, and built-in Computer Use in one. Learn what's new, how it compares to GPT-5.2, and how to access it affordably via GPT Proto.\\\",\\\"keywords\\\":\\\"GPT-5.4\\\"}\",\"createTime\":\"2026-03-09 18:15:12\",\"editTime\":\"2026-03-09 18:16:42\",\"status\":1,\"language\":\"en\",\"appId\":\"gptproto.com\",\"uuidCode\":\"2e94456653884845a33d9a282eae857c\",\"author\":{\"id\":4,\"name\":\"Tiffany Layne\",\"avatar\":\"https://heyoo.oss-ap-southeast-1.aliyuncs.com/2025/09/23/53a0ab25c3c743f382d6435763ec236d.png\",\"profile\":\"Tiffany Layne (Pseudonym Tiffany) studied Information Systems at Ludwig Maximilian University of Munich and earned an M.A. in Digital Marketing. Since 2013, she has been working as an editor, translator, and marketing strategist for software and AI platforms. She writes high-quality guides and insights on API-based services, AI model usage, system stability, and digital business applications, providing readers with both technical know-how and practical perspectives in the AI industry.\"},\"introduction\":\"\u003ch2\u003eTL;DR:\u003c/h2\u003e\\n\u003cp\u003eGPT-5.4 is OpenAI's newest model that merges reasoning, coding, and desktop control into one. It outperforms GPT-5.2 across most benchmarks, supports a 1M token context window, and is now available through platforms like GPT Proto at reduced API rates.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"type\":\"blog\"},{\"id\":2864,\"authorId\":1,\"authorName\":\"Tiffany Layne\",\"image\":null,\"authorAvatar\":null,\"simplifiedName\":\"Everything You Need to Know about Nano Banana 2\",\"traditionalName\":\"Everything You Need to Know about Nano Banana 2\",\"englishName\":\"Everything You Need to Know about Nano Banana 2\",\"name\":\"Everything You Need to Know about Nano Banana 2\",\"shortSimplifiedContent\":\"\",\"shortTraditionalContent\":\"\",\"shortEnglishContent\":\"\",\"shortContent\":\"\",\"contentType\":\"html\",\"releaseTime\":\"2026-03-05 14:58:14\",\"readCount\":1,\"likeCount\":1,\"commentCount\":1,\"categoryID\":199,\"categoryName\":\"gptproto.com\",\"logo\":\"https://oss.gptproto.com/gptproto/ai-draw/java/test//2026/03/05/7cd21c4a663a48bcb32bb3ea0dec36c5.jpg\",\"metaTitle\":null,\"metaDescription\":null,\"url\":null,\"categoryVos\":null,\"tagVos\":null,\"categoryUuid\":\"gptproto.com\",\"uuid\":\"nano-banana-2-guide\",\"seo\":\"{\\\"metaTitle\\\":\\\"Nano Banana 2 Review: Features, Real-World Tests \u0026 Everything You Need to Know\\\",\\\"metaDescription\\\":\\\"Nano Banana 2 (Gemini 3.1 Flash Image) is Google's fastest, most affordable AI image model yet — ranked #1 on Arena. Read our full feature breakdown, real test results, Pro comparison, and why developers are turning to GPT Proto for unified AI access.\\\",\\\"keywords\\\":\\\"nano banana 2\\\"}\",\"createTime\":\"2026-03-05 14:02:57\",\"editTime\":\"2026-03-05 14:58:14\",\"status\":1,\"language\":\"en\",\"appId\":\"gptproto.com\",\"uuidCode\":\"d025b33dc9ac495288e763fc725c0581\",\"author\":{\"id\":4,\"name\":\"Tiffany Layne\",\"avatar\":\"https://heyoo.oss-ap-southeast-1.aliyuncs.com/2025/09/23/53a0ab25c3c743f382d6435763ec236d.png\",\"profile\":\"Tiffany Layne (Pseudonym Tiffany) studied Information Systems at Ludwig Maximilian University of Munich and earned an M.A. in Digital Marketing. Since 2013, she has been working as an editor, translator, and marketing strategist for software and AI platforms. She writes high-quality guides and insights on API-based services, AI model usage, system stability, and digital business applications, providing readers with both technical know-how and practical perspectives in the AI industry.\"},\"introduction\":\"\u003ch2\u003eIntroduction\u003c/h2\u003e\\n\u003cp\u003eOn February 26, 2026, Google DeepMind quietly launched Nano Banana 2 \u0026mdash; and the AI community noticed immediately. Within hours of release, it climbed to the top of the Arena text-to-image leaderboard, outscoring both GPT-image-1 and Nano Banana Pro with a score of 1,279. The official technical name is \u003cstrong\u003e\u003ca href=\\\"https://gptproto.com/model/google/gemini-3.1-flash-image-preview\\\"\u003eGemini 3.1 Flash Image\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/strong\u003e (also known as Gemini 3.1 Flash Image Preview).\u003c/p\u003e\\n\u003cp\u003eFor developers, designers, and content creators who need fast, high-quality image generation at scale, Nano Banana 2 answers a question that has lingered for a while: can you get Pro-level image quality without Pro-level speed limits and costs? The answer, it turns out, is yes.\u003c/p\u003e\\n\u003cp\u003e\u0026nbsp;\u003c/p\u003e\",\"type\":\"blog\"}],\"children\":\"$L23\"}]\n"])</script><script>self.__next_f.push([1,"23:[\"$\",\"$L24\",null,{}]\n5:E{\"digest\":\"NEXT_REDIRECT;replace;/;307;\"}\n"])</script></body></html>